Issues.Body:
Affected Package
@angular/Renderer2
### Description

I am trying to use Renderer2 to wrap each child of my `<ng-content>` in a `div` element

```  
ngAfterContentInit(): void {
    let container = document.getElementById('smart-container-id');
    let content: HTMLCollection = container.children;
    let count = content.length;
    console.log('There are ' + count + ' children')
    for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) {
      let wrapper = this.renderer.createElement('div');
      wrapper.id = 'foo' + i;
      this.renderer.appendChild(wrapper, content.item(i));
      this.renderer.appendChild(container, wrapper);
    }
```

I expect each of the 6 children components to be wrapped with a `div` and an id of `fooX`

when I run this code I get

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/27922019/76126920-645dec00-5fce-11ea-8700-df9c821e77f6.png)


As you can see 3 of the children have not been wrapped, as well as div `foo2` is now a child of `foo4` and `foo4` being a child of `foo5` 

